comment.body:
1 - check the sub's wiki; 


2 - buy tickets directly on site. There is a queue, but the times are always reasonable for both cash and card payments; 


3 - you can buy tickets for the dome and the lift directly at St. Peter's (2 different tickets); 


4 - No, the ticket is different. [Official info](https://www.omniavaticanrome.org/it/cards/il-carcer-tullianum);


5 - Very easy. One of the 2 Italian railway companies offers the [train + bus](https://www.trenitalia.com/it/treni_regionali/lazio/ville-di-tivoli-link.html) solution;


6 - It is the Sunday market of Porta Portese. I don't like these things so I don't know what to say.
